# SAIR — The Foundation for Science and AI Research
> Co-founded by Terence Tao, SAIR unites Nobel, Turing, and Fields laureates to scale scientific discovery with AI, and ground AI in science. Tagline: "Grounding Intelligence. Scaling Discovery."
SAIR (the Foundation for Science and AI Research) is a non-profit that supports research programs and connects world-leading scientists with enterprise partners to advance the theoretical foundations of AI and unlock new frontiers in scientific discovery. Terence Tao, alongside Nobel, Turing, and Fields laureates, leads SAIR in advancing scientific discovery and guiding AI with scientific principles for humanity.
This file is a plain-text map of the site for AI agents and crawlers. The main website is a JavaScript-rendered single-page app; the Markdown shadows linked below carry the same content as readable text.
## Core programs
- Research Network: An ecosystem uniting Nobel, Turing, and Fields Medal laureates with pioneering scientists across disciplines.
- Corporate Partnership: Membership program connecting Fortune 500 companies & AI industry leaders.
- Global Conferences: Amplifying new discoveries through worldwide awards, events, and media.
How it works: Fund (support frontier research with funding, AI tools, and compute) → Collaborate (academia and enterprise working side-by-side on real data and experiments) → Ecosystem (breakthroughs flow back to inspire new research and inform industry).
