## Competitions
- [Inverse Galois Problem (IGP24)](https://competition.sair.foundation/competitions/igp24): A mathematical discovery challenge to expand the known map of degree-24 equations and their hidden symmetries.
- [Modular Arithmetic Challenge](https://competition.sair.foundation/competitions/modular-arithmetic-challenge): Can a neural network learn to compute (a × b) mod p for integers hundreds of digits long? An open probe of where exact machine reasoning breaks down.
- [Mathematics Distillation Challenge — Equational Theories (Stage 1)](https://competition.sair.foundation/competitions/mathematics-distillation-challenge-equational-theories-stage1): Submit a single knowledge prompt that guides an LLM to decide whether one equation implies another. The prompt must include placeholders for Equation 1 and Equation 2 so each evaluation problem can be inserted automatically. SAIR's first competition, announced by Terence Tao.
- [Mathematics Distillation Challenge — Equational Theories (Stage 2)](https://competition.sair.foundation/competitions/mathematics-distillation-challenge-equational-theories-stage2): Submit a solver that, for each pair of equations, produces a machine-verified Lean 4 certificate, adjudicated by a deterministic Lean judge.
